docs.abstract: About 50 people gathered this month for a party in the upscale suburb of Westport, then scattered across the region and the world, taking the coronavirus with them.
docs.snippet: About 50 people gathered this month for a party in the upscale suburb of Westport, then scattered across the region and the world, taking the coronavirus with them.
docs.lead_paragraph: About 50 guests gathered on March 5 at a home in the stately suburb of Westport, Conn., to toast the hostess on her 40th birthday and greet old friends, including one visiting from South Africa. They shared reminiscences, a lavish buffet and, unknown to anyone, the coronavirus.

headline.main: Party Zero: How a Soirée in Connecticut Became a ‘Super Spreader’

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A group of bipartisan House lawmakers on Monday outlined a plan to stem the flow of counterfeit products from China and other countries into the United States by making e-commerce companies such as Amazon legally liable for fake goods sold on their websites.

docs.abstract: In wresting control of the administration’s haphazard response to the virus, Mike Pence has taken on a familiar role as the president’s political janitor.
docs.snippet: In wresting control of the administration’s haphazard response to the virus, Mike Pence has taken on a familiar role as the president’s political janitor.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Vice President Mike Pence has long been a one-man political cleanup crew for President Trump. From his day trip last fall to Turkey to negotiate a cease-fire in northern Syria to his takeover of the chaotic presidential transition, Mr. Pence is used to being diverted from his reliably anodyne schedule.

headline.main: Pence, a Loyalist Tapped for Coronavirus Effort, Adds to Trump’s Mixed Messages
headline.print_headline: Pence’s New Virus Duty: Cleaning Up Messaging
